reviews.text: Despite not being able to see much at night, it was still pretty cool. I'd definitely recommend going during the daytime so you can see a lot more of the views. It would be nice if the interior lights were dimmed a little bit at night. Ah well! Good reason to come back later! 😁
Very nice view! I love how you have two levels in case you are scared of heights or you want to see better. It shows. Really cool info in the ball, and it's really cool! 10/10 would recommend!

If you are already in the area this is a great 15 minute attraction. Free but parking can be challenging ~ however, only cost us $1 and there was a walkway over the road to get there.  You take an elevator up to the 4th level inside the sphere for a really nice 360 view of downtown Knoxville. Would have been great if they had washed the windows. Nice area with walking paths,  concert pavilion at the base. Interesting facts posted inside the sphere regarding the World's Fair and Knoxville in general.

It's really cool this is free to visit. The Space Needle in Seattle from the '62 World Fair, I think, charges upwards of $10 to go up to the top. The Sunsphere isn't as tall but it's tall enough to see the beauty of Knoxville. At the top in the visiting level there's information screens around that correspond to various sites in the area such as the veterans monument. It was really cool and a great way to be introduced to Knoxville and it's point of interest.
This is a cool way to learn a little history about Knoxville and get to see some of the city from above. Plus, it's free!!!! Worth checking out if your in town.

The exhibits here are well-designed, historically significant, and locally-relevant. The museum is one of the smaller but more focused types. In this case, the focus is on Tennessee history. That being said, the museum is hardly small, as it takes up most of a city block. 

You can view the whole thing in an afternoon if you aren't going to interact with everything. If you are the sort of person who has to 100% every museum you visit (like me!), then this one can keep you occupied for an entire day.

A museum is an odd sell for a review. If you are big on museums, then you'll love this one. If you aren't, then this one won't change your mind. Ultimately, I decided to give it a five-star rating because it is an excellent specimen of what it sets out to be. Did I like it better than the Smithsonian or the British Museum? No, but that doesn't mean that it deserves any less than a perfect score because it treats its' chosen subject with reverence, respect, and thoroughness. 

In short, I would recommend it to anyone interested in what this place is offering.

This is a well done highly produced low-tech experience. It was refreshing to experience the museum without an in your face technology overlay. They have great videos and many of the artifacts are priceless.

I especially loved the infographics. Especially, interested in the graphic that showed how the majority of the region chose to stay part of the United States of America during the civil war.

My takeaway from the museum is that East Tennessee is a rugged community that breaks many stereotypes.

The quality of the museum's production reflects the quality of the regions people.
Wonderful place to spend the afternoon. Exhibits cover many periods of East TN history. We've been several times and always enjoy going back.
We visited this museum from Florida. So much history...and very well put together. The staff welcomed us with a smile. We enjoyed everything about this museum.

Came here on a Sunday and was pleasantly surprised that entrance was by donation only - I really appreciate that a number of attractions in Knoxville take this approach. It makes visiting so seamless and easy! 

I likely could have spent more time here, as this museum is a wealth of information - the museum charts Tennessee history all the way from the earliest indigenous peoples up to the modern era. There's even a little section talking about the rich history of country music and the prominent artists that hailed from Tennessee - you can even hear some clips of songs! Really terrific stuff. 

A must see if you're in the area. The museum is right in the middle of the charming downtown Knoxville area, as well, so you'll have plenty more to do within walking distance once you're done.

They are the best where you can go for a real "slice & a Coke".  
Delicious, as always.  The most consistent pizza place, that we have eaten at, for a long way around.  They totally dwarf the little take-out  "chains" on taste alone.
My whole family loves this place. It’s a gem. The pizza isn’t like any pizza you’ve ever had before, but it is AMAZING. You have to try it. Highly recommended.

The best NY-style slice I’ve had in Knoxville. It’s up there with DeSano (Nashville) in terms of great thin crust pizzas. Crust is perfect, sauce flavor & amount just right, plenty of cheese and pepperoni. I look forward to bringing my wife next time. Today was a great value: 2 generous slices and a fountain drink for $6.18 all in. Nicely done, guys!!

Very disappointing  ! I got a 18" Pizza the crust was burnt a little and the Pizza had very little tomato sauce on it and did not taste good at all.  Not sure what I paid for the Coke put it is .50 cents to get a refill.  Not worth it ! 

A store bought Pizza or a frozen Pizza would have been better than what I bought from this guy. The woman up Front to take your order isn't that nice either. 

You can do Better else were. Even Papa  Murphy's Pizza better than what I had today.  

Don't Go Their, you will be sorry. 

There prices is way to high and when you leave, they can't even tell you to come back or  even tell you have a nice day.

This was my first visit their and spent over $30.00. Sorry I even went.

Wish I had my money back.

Do Not  Go Period  ! I will never go back.

A very sorry business and they won't be one for long ! They don't Appreciate who gives them a Paycheck. 

They have a very Sorry,  Attitude  !

The pizza was good. The back end of the crust was perfect, but the main part of the crust that the toppings were on was a little soggy and floppy, but it was a thin crust pizza so I expected a little of that, just not to the degree that I had it. The ingredients themselves were, individually, delicious, but I could only eat 2 pieces 😊 overall, I think you'll enjoy it

Service is amazing and so if the food. We come here a lot and are always satisfied. Food was taking a while to come out tonight but the team brought us something to snack on and offered free dessert. It honestly wasn’t a big deal to us but we appreciated the communication and care. I hate I don’t remember our waitress name but thank you sweet pea. We all thought it was cute she kept saying sweet pea, it make the kids giggle a little.

Food was delicious! The TN corn pudding is a must have ! The ribs are fantastic and the brisket and pork are expertly smoked. Tammy, the general manager, is so nice! Our server, Tim, is top notch. Great atmosphere. Will definitely go back !!

The bad: A little pricy for what you get and waits can be long. I have had some very unenthusiastic servers who seemed like they wanted to be anywhere but here.

The good: the young lady who is smaller built with dark hair who does carry out is exceptional. I only get carryout now and its always nice when she is working. Very personable and pleasant. The food is also very yummy...try their beer muffins if you like semi sweet bread

During a roadtrip I used Google to see high star ranked restaurants and ended up finding this one. This was a pretty easy restaurant to find and worth the stop, I walked in and the hostess gave me options for seating or to go towards the bar so I went with the bar area. When I sat down it wasn't too busy, but it took a tad in order to get water and a drink order but after that the service was quick and good. The look of the restaurant was not really different than any traditional restaurant, but it was clean and the bar had a cool design. Now the food I got steak and rips and both were very well cooked and delicious l, steak was seasoned well and cooked perfect, the ribs were delicious could have used more sauce and some of the pieces were over cooked but still very delicious. Over all delicious place to stop and eat.

Enjoyed a nice lunch there today with my brother.  Our server was Sandra and she treated us very well, I wish more servers were like her.  I had the beef brisket plate with Mac & cheese and coleslaw.  The beef was well smoked, had a nice flavor and just the right moisture.  The breads were good, I liked the beer muffin.  We also gas a slice of key lime pie.  We left full.

I love the Chop House. The food is hands down the best in Ann Arbor. We always go for the cheese platter appetizer and it is some of the best you will find. The prices are a little steep but once you taste the food, it is well worth it. The cocktails are alright and they need a bit more mixing before being served as they aren't a uniform flavor but outside of that, I highly recommend this place for an anniversary or birthday or just a nice date. Their cigar lounge is high quality and the atmosphere is perfect. I will always come back to this place.

A couple weeks ago, we enjoyed a dinner elsewhere in Ann Arbor and decided to head to Chop House after for an espresso and cigar. After a half mile walk we arrive to find out the cigar bar is non smoking due to a private party. Fine. No problem, we should have called. Tonight, we did the same thing. Except we called first to make sure the cigar lounge was open, we called, yes it’s open. Perfect, we walk there. Guess what, closed. Continuous bad service from this place. It’s overpriced we all know that, but it used to at least have good service. Not anymore. Save yourself the dull experience and go to the steak house around the corner.

The steaks were tender and thick and all of the appetizers were great. We also had very good service. It's a pretty fancy establishment. And they offer great discounts for birthdays. Roughly enough to make the birthday persons meal free, given that it's on the actual birthday.

Went here on two occasions. One was my girlfriend's birthday. It was a wonderful time. The staff were friendly and very speedy, and food was amazing. However, when I went for my club's business conference, it was a bit hectic-- understandably. Several orders were messed up, but they were corrected surprisingly fast. Overall, a great place to dine!

Pretty awesome place. Went doing restaurant week where you get a 3 course meal or something for $28. I ended up taking my wife for her birthday and got their birthday discount. Got the 11oz steak, calamari, mashed potatoes, and asparagus. All was good. Bathroom was nice and clean but a little intimate since everything is in one little corner. Ambience was great. Recommend seeing Kiara for best service. Overall great experience.

The food was great. The prices very reasonable. The service was EXTREMELY slow. Our waitress took over 15 min. to bring beverages over 20 min. to take our order, and 30 min. to bring bread to the table, the bread did not arrive until my husband requested it from another server. She did not check back on the table in a timely fashion for drink refills. Nor did she suggestive sale or offer dessert options. I watched other parties of equal and larger size seated around us receive better quality service. We were a party of 8 all African American with two veterans. I was truly disappointed in the service. Due to our party size we we're charged18% gratuity, Sugestion, diversity training in providing EQUAL quality service to ALL customers.

I really loved this place! The food was fresh, the seafood was terrific, and the service was well above par! What a nice place. 
There was a minor incident with my soup but the manager was very apologetic and more than rectified the issue!

2nd visit was during dinner hour. I was SO unimpressed! It was a night and day experience. Steak was fatty and flavorless. Oysters were not even separated from their shell, hardly clean.

I had a decent experience here. I couldn't give it 5 stars because our waitress seemed a bit frazzled and I was overcharged for beverages. I was charged for 8 @$3/drink when my party only had 5....So, in order to diffuse any confusion of summoning the manager, I just deducted them from my server's tip.🤷🏾‍♀️ The biggest highlight was my Sunshine Sangria. It was pretty tasty...albeit, I'm not a huge drinker, so it may have been mediocre to an avid drinker's taste, but I liked it. Perhaps, next time, I'd go with a smaller crowd to see if that makes a difference in the atmosphere.
A excellent experience! Absolutely the best calamari in the world! Staff is nothing but the best! I just love this place

Great food but the service is so god  awful it’s not worth the money. Made a reservation a week in advance and the hostess blew us off, made us wait a long time and when we pushed for our reserved table gave us the worst one on the house. However when someone they knew came in with no reservation they got seated right away in the main dining room.  The manager was clueless. Never going back. Ruth Chris or Sperry are far more respectful to there customers.

Amazing service!! The kind friendly person  working led me through the menu with excitement & shared enthusiasm about what I ordered. Food was spot on! Got some tacos, I tried 3 different kinds. Super tasty & filled with flavor! I can’t wait to return!

Love this place!! Such an awesome vegan/vegetarian option and it is nice and cozy. The variety of options is excellent. We have tried every single taco choice on the menu! Their juices and smoothies are excellent as well. It's never like crazy crowded but there are always people rotating in and out no matter the time we have gone. Highly recommend.

Great service good prices. The menu is fully vegan but can be vegetarian-ized. Lots of fresh justices or smoothies. Good amount of seating and you can have food delivered through a variety of services. Street parking can be tough but you know, welcome to Chicago.

Overall I thought the place was great. It's not huge but they use all the space to have  a lot of tables. Staff is very polite and the flavors are so authentic. Some "meats" have a different size than the original, but overall the texture is very true to the original dish which honestly surprised me, especially for the chicharron. The only things I will say could be improved is waiting when the restaurant is full, and desserts. We tried a couple different desserts and they really weren't very good. The texture and the flavor were a little off. That said, the food was very good and the prices were very affordable. For some dishes you honestly wouldn't be able to tell you're eating a vegan dish.

Delicious food, easy ways to veganize most dishes and the staff is knowledgeable about the menu making it easy to order! The staff is always very friendly especially Fernando! Love coming here and recommending it to everyone I know!

Always love the food and wine selection, the service is typically hit or miss. They either know and care about their dishes, drinks or have no personality and no idea except that it's raw fish... Overall, more good times then bad they will continue to have my business.

I honestly don't know why people love Nama. I have been multiple times and the sushi is always disappointing. I got the fish tacos this time, because of Taco Tuesday, and they were pretty good. If you are a real sushi fan, I would say avoid Nama sushi. It's always sugary, which covers up the lack of flavor from the fish. They pile on a lot of extra stuff but somehow it's still bland. I think a lot of Americans like their sushi this way, but I certainly don't. Order off the non-sushi menu and you will probably have a better experience.

The best sushi experience so far!! The chefs are very accommodating and friendly!  Definitely my favorite place. Food is amazingly good and innovative! Talking to the sushi chefs is a big plus and I feel like I’m with good friends sitting at the sushi bar. If you haven’t eaten here you should!
Best sushi in Knoxville. Very fresh fish with lots of creative menu options. Small, peaceful, friendly environment that's great for business lunches or dinner. Highly recommended!

Arrived at about 6:10 p.m. on Thursday. It was 1.5 hr wait. So left without service. It's very good sushi on the pricey side. But you have to arrive earlier or later in the evening to take advantage of the reduced price days. I like arriving later in the evenings...like 9ish to get best service. Try the chef's special where they custom make sushi - hint: tell them you favorite rolls and they can make something around that. Surf and turf tempura appetizers is great as well as the dumpling platter. They have vegan options and hot food choices as well.

Super chill atmosphere to say the least. Saturday night there was actually a live DJ and live cover One Man Band! We were celebrating my sister's birthday and we got a nicely spaced 8 passenger Roundtable which is rare but definitely appreciated. 

The space is very large and they even have clear glass separating walls which adds a modern cool futuristic look. The bathrooms are also decent in this place, at least talking from the man's perspective. 

The food was surely awesome as well and the service that we got was complete. It DID TAKE about 10 minutes for me to get my initial drink but it was kind of special so I did let it slide. If you're curious to know it was a peach Tea unsweetened, which is not one of their usual and had to be made at the bar special hand crafted! Yeah I got it like that I suppose.

This is good for the families with kids and adults alike. I don't believe it gets too rowdy and if you do not want the lie I've seen you can skip right next door about 20 steps away to Calhoun's, also Family Restaurant and owned by the same company.  

Things to try are definitely the Thunder Road wings with I believe it's called the Thunder Road sauce. And they also have great fries and hamburgers any one of them you try you will love! 
ENJOY!

Fine joint. I sat at the bar and enjoyed a seriously large IPA. 
Service was attentive, if not very informative.
But, I'll go back again. It's a really nice place.

Laid back atmosphere. Great for watching a game on TV! The burger my husband ordered was good, and the calzone I got was alright. I feel like a lot of the food items don't get enough cooking attention (development of flavor). However, it is a great place to hangout with family and friends and grab a bite on a weekend!

Smoky Mountain Brewery has a great selection of hamburgers, sandwiches, and entrees. They have a very nice variety of appetizers too.  Of course, the craft brews are excellent.  Check on the brewmasters specials for a unique beer.
Very loving and beautiful company Teresa Lynn Baird Maynard need I say more.... Enjoying adult beverages with my sister and her friend.

Trio has a great atmosphere with an awesome staff. We came in for the New Years preset menu which sounded divine! Our first courses were great, however our steak came out over cooked and we were quite bummed. Fortunately the chef came by and asked us how our experience was, and he immediately sent out a new perfectly cooked steak and won us over! The food really is incredible and the chefs do a great job. We will be back and greatly appreciate the customer service!

Though the portions seemed small, the food was very good at Trio. Our server forgot about us a few times (neglecting to bring drinks or check in about the meal), but she was very friendly and knowledgeable. Probably just overworked. The atmosphere was nice, too, though it was exceptionally loud.
Had the fish special. It was great. Grouper asparagus and potatoes. The fish was crisp on the outside and soft on the inside.

We tried this place because the chef of a restaurant in Raleigh, NC we love recommended it. The food was absolutely delicious and the hostess/host were so welcoming and kind. Unfortunately, we had a rude waiter who acted like we were inconveniencing him every time we ordered. He was very short and made a snide comment after we asked for a recommendation on an appetizer and we went for the opposite of his choice. We didn’t pick his recommendation bc he didn’t seem enthused or that he cared what we ordered. This restaurant is in my top 3 favorites while staying in Jackson; just unfortunate we had a negative encounter with a server.
Good food, reasonable price, and it's Jackson hole.

We had the best time at Finn’s and enjoyed all aspects of our time there. We originally had a reservation but went for an early dinner and decided to sit on the tavern side since it wasn’t very busy yet (around 5 pm) - the tavern side is pretty laid back and seat yourself. Make sure you get there before 7 if you don't have a reservation. This was a Saturday night and the tavern filled up quickly. I had never been to the restaurant before Finns but my husband had and said the place had totally transformed. They preserved the great aspects of the historic building and updated where it needed to be updated. I had the salmon special for dinner which was topped with a smoked bacon maple sauce. This was one of the best dishes I’ve had in Knoxville. If they have a special while you are there - get it! I guarantee it’s going to be the best thing they have to offer. We stayed for quite a while that night and moved over to one of the booth tables to have some drinks after dinner - they have everything from cocktails to Irish beers. The whole experience was amazing and we have plans to go back this weekend!! Don’t miss out on this experience.

Quite pleased with the entire dining experience. This is genuine Irish cuisine. I ordered the Irish Breakfast Plate. My wife the Corn Beef Hash. This was for Saturday brunch. Excellent quality all around. Good service and the Irish owner greeted us several times during the experience. I felt the price was on target and the historical home Finn's is located in sets a fantastic mood. This is an excellent event location with large private room connected to bar with plenty of natural light. We will have to try Finns at the dinner hour. I'm sure it won't disappoint.

Phenomenal! I wish I'd have gone sooner! The space is beautiful. The food was sublime! The drinks were great and our waiter was wonderful! I had the cottage pie (much like a shepherd's pie) which I highly recommend. It was delicious!  We also had the muscles appetizer and my husband had a pork special. Nothing disappointed. Can't wait to go back. Next time I'll have to be sure to leave room for dessert.

Went to this place that was once the Bakers-Peters Jazz Club, now converted into an Irish pub/restaurant. I was mostly pleased with the repurposing of this historic home but verdict is still out on dishes they typically serve. On St. Pat's Day they had very limited menu due to size of crowd, which would make it impractical to offer full menu. Still, a fun place with live music and now run by the former owner of Irish Times in Knox.

Went there for St Patrick’s event on 3/16. It was very busy with event outside in a tent and live music inside. They were sold out of all the popular menu items! They were WAY understaffed for the size of the event! Incredibly slow service but our server was very apologetic. She was clearly frustrated with the restaurant’s lack of proper preparation. I will be willing to try it again but would recommend avoiding any holidays that typically involve drinking.

Don't expect great service, but food was excellent and atmosphere was perfect for our date night. This would've been an easy 5 star rating if it wasn't for the lack of service and teamwork. Coming from a restaurant service background, my basics as a customer tonight were not met, or even cared about for that matter. Our food took 30 minutes to come out. We saw tables of 4+ sit down, eat, and leave before I got a beer (my husband got one, but I was never asked). IF we go again...I will do my research and request the best server/waiter. We didn't have an appetizer because we planned on enjoying a beer together while our entrees were being prepared. Again, very disappointed in our server, surrounding servers (no teamwork), and management.

Edited to remove waiter's name. 😏

First time going tonight and it was amazing. The service and food both 5 stars! Our waitress Elizabeth was very knowledgeable about the food and drinks and her suggestions were amazing. Will definitely be going back!

A favorite of mine. I am a veteran and spent some time in Germany. Loved Germany, love this restaurant. Met the 'new' owners a few nights ago. He seems nice.The food is good again. It wasn't for awhile. If you want some simple German authenticity, this is your place.
Great place! New owners are wonderful. I have brought a group to eat there, and everyone loves the food. Service is absolutely wonderful. Looking forward to this year's opening of the patio!

Fantastic service, great conversation. My German is mainly small conversational and basic, but out waiter had a great attitude and conversed with me. The food was fantastic top notch curry wurst. I also had forgotten my to go box on the table and he ran it out to me in my truck. Fantastic!

With a party of four we visited Kitchen 919 this evening. A truly wonderful experience. We ordered the lamb chops, tenderloin and prime rib. All were cooked to perfection and the presentation was outstanding. We ordered a dessert to share which was the hibiscus creme burlee and was enjoyed by all. Amy was our server and she did an excellent job. She was very attentive. We definitely will be returning.
Always wonderful! Sent daughter and husband for an anniversary gift, and it did not disappoint! Great food and drink, wonderful service!

Ive been here 3 times now and each time is better than the last. The food is perfect every time and so are the drinks. You can count on great service as well. Highly recommend if you haven’t been!! :)

Absolutely exquisite dining and architectural experience! Everything is top notch!!! Ask for Lisa as your server and definitely go upstairs to peak at their remodeling! Their sister restaurant is Seasons Cafe in turkey creek and both these restaurants are premium and my most favorite restaurants in Knoxville!

Kitchen 919 is an upscale, fine-dining establishment. It occupies a space which previously housed The Orangery in Homberg Place, just off Kingston Pike in the Bearden district of Knoxville. Had the chicken with couscous and vegetable medley and an Italian sparkling wine which complemented the entree nicely. Servings were very generous and our server was knowledgeable and efficient. The low-volume jazz from piano and bass was a nice accompaniment to a delightful gastronomic experience!
